  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Rational Requirements Composer is a collaborative toolset that supports teams to create a glossary to build&#xD;
    consistent, common terminology for the project. Requirement context is enhanced by capturing common terminology related&#xD;
    to requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Benefits of Using Rational Requirements Composer for Glossaries&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Capture terms that can be reused across projects and glossaries.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reference any requirement artifact and link a term to it to provide context.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Link terms to other terms which are related or are synonyms.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Create a Glossary&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Create the glossary by following the instructions in the Rational Requirements Composer Help\Creating a Glossary.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Create Terms&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Terms&amp;nbsp;can be independent of a glossary. They provide consistent terminology for a project. A term can&amp;nbsp;also&#xD;
    exist in one or more glossaries. Create new terms by following the instructions in the Rational Requirements composer&#xD;
    Help\Creating Terms.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Look up Terms&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Terms&amp;nbsp;can be reviewed from any document in Rational Requirements Composer. Look up terms by following Help\Looking&#xD;
    up Terms.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Link to Terms&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Various requirements artifacts&amp;nbsp;can be linked to a glossary to provide further information about the artifact. Link&#xD;
    to terms by following the instructions in the Rational Requirements Composer Help\Linking to Terms.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
